# {{.Name}}

Shared protobuf contracts generated by [JGO](https://github.com/eyesofblue/jgo).

- Project type: `proto`
- Go module: `{{.Module}}`
- Go version: `{{.GoVersion}}` (JGO minimum: `1.24.0`)

This repository contains contracts and generated Go protobuf/gRPC packages only. It has no server process and no JGO runtime dependency. Both gRPC servers and callers import packages under `{{.Module}}/gen/pb/...`.

## Workflow

```bash
jgo tools install # once per Go development environment
jgo rpc pbapi add RPCName --service {{.ServiceName}}
# The initial {{.ServiceName}}.Echo example is retained. Add more Services to
# this repository when needed:
jgo rpc pbservice add AnotherService
# Edit request fields and response business fields from number 3.
jgo rpc generate
jgo list
go test ./...
```

Every RPC response must contain non-optional `int32 code = 1` and `string msg = 2`. Business fields start at number 3. `jgo rpc generate` lints the contracts and updates `gen/pb`; it does not generate a service implementation or transport adapter in a proto project. Run `jgo new` only once for the repository; `pbservice add` adds subsequent protobuf Services.

Commit the `.proto` files and generated `gen/pb` packages, tag the module, then require that version from server and caller projects.
